A N A C T
RELATING TO EDUCATION -- HEALTH AND SAFETY OF PUPILS
Introduced By: Representatives Casimiro, Noret, Spears, Donovan, Carson, Morales,
Solomon, and Shanley
Date Introduced: February 07, 2025
Referred To: House Education
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 16-21 of the General Laws entitled "Health and Safety of Pupils" is
2 hereby amended by adding thereto the following section:
3 16-21-8.1. Certified school psychologist.
4 Effective September 1, 2027, each school system in the state shall employ a minimum of
5 one certified school psychologist, certified by the state department of elementary and secondary
6 education, for every five hundred (500) students enrolled in the school.
7 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
